## Proposed Rewrite Structure (~3 pages / ~900 words)

```
1. INTRODUCTION & PROBLEM STATEMENT (~250 words)
   → Open with Prestea: mining, forest loss, climate stress
   → Frame the problem as a food security crisis
   → State why existing approaches fail (blanket N, no spatial data)
   → Mirror ACCI language naturally

2. OBJECTIVES (~100 words)
   → 3 specific, measurable objectives
   → Each one ends with a deliverable, not a concept

3. METHODOLOGY (~300 words)
   → Study area: Prestea specifics (coordinates, climate, crops)
   → Data: Sentinel-2 L2A, 16-feature vector, NDVI stratification
   → Model: VegHealthCNN 1D-CNN architecture (brief)
   → Validation: Spatial Block CV with GroupKFold
   → Application: VRA prescription logic with NDRE

4. EXPECTED OUTCOMES & SIGNIFICANCE (~150 words)
   → Quantified: "estimated 15-30% nitrogen savings"
   → Climate link: N₂O mitigation + yield adaptation
   → Scalability: open-source, replicable across West Africa
   → ACCI alignment: explicit

5. TIMELINE (~50 words or table)
   → 4-phase timeline across the MPhil duration

6. BUDGET JUSTIFICATION (~50 words)
   → Fieldwork, GPU compute, conference dissemination
```

